related_questions.question: What are price extensions?
related_questions.snippet: What are Price Extensions? Price Extensions are extra snippets of information about your specific products or services that can be added to your AdWords text ads. They initially beta-tested in English and $USD, but are now publicly available to all advertisers in 24 languages and currencies.Jul 27, 2018

related_questions.question: How many callout extensions can you have?
related_questions.snippet: You can feature up to four callouts in your ad, each limited to 25 characters each, and must have at least two callouts for them to display. Callout extensions can be used with other ad formats, like sitelinks, and are created, scheduled and managed within the Ad Extensions tab.Sep 17, 2018

related_questions.question: What are structured snippets?
related_questions.snippet: Structured snippets allow your ads to highlight specific aspects of your products and services. These ad extensions provide context on the nature and variety of your products and services before visitors click through to your site. Each snippet contains a header and list of features you would like to highlight.Jan 25, 2019

answer_box.title: About affiliate location extensions - Google Ads Help
answer_box.snippet: If you're a manufacturer who sells products through major retail chains, you can use affiliate location extensions to help people find nearby stores that sell your product. If you want to advertise your own business location, use location extensions instead.
